contentrichtext.text: {{Wiktionary|Dora}} '''Dora''' may refer to: * [[Dora (name)]] {{TOC right}} ==Places== ;Australia *[[Lake Dora (Tasmania)]] *[[Lake Dora (Western Australia)]] ;United States *[[Dora, Alabama]] *[[Dora, Arkansas]] *[[Dora, Missouri]] *[[Dora, New Mexico]] ;Other countries *[[Dora, Baghdad]], Iraq *[[Dora, Cyprus]] *[[Dora, Lebanon]] *[[Dorasan]] or Mount Dora, a hill in South Korea *Dora, Ancient Greek and Roman name for a former town; see [[Tel Dor]], an archaeological site ==Fiction== *Dora, fictional character in the webcomic ''[[Erfworld]]'' *Dora Bianchi, fictional character in the webcomic ''[[Questionable Content]]'' *[[Doraemon]], Japanese anime and manga *[[Dora the Explorer]], American television program aimed at young children *[[Nymphadora|Nymphadora Tonks]], fictional character in the Harry Potter universe *Dora, one of [[Lazarus Long]]'s primary spacecraft, and her sentient integral computer, in various interrelated novels by science fiction author Robert A. Heinlein * Dora Spenlow, fictional character in ''David Copperfield'' by Charles Dickens ==War== *[[Defence of the Realm Act 1914]] (DORA), British war legislation adopted in August 1914 *[[Dora (artillery)]], 80cm German railway artillery pieces *[[DORA 1]] and DORA 2, German U-boat bases in Trondheim, Norway *Fw 190 D "Dora", model of [[Focke-Wulf Fw 190]] German fighter aircraft *[[Mittelbau-Dora]], World War II concentration camp *Dora, code name of World War II Soviet intelligence agent [[Alexander Rado]] == Other uses == * [[Dora (grape)]], another name for the Italian wine grape Fortana * [[668 Dora]], main belt asteroid * "Dora", 1984 song by [[Ambitious Lovers]] from the album ''Envy'' * [[Dora (case study)]] of Sigmund Freud, described in ''A Case of Hysteria'' * [[Dora Mavor Moore Award]] for Canadian professional theatre * [[EV-DO]] Revision A standard, abbreviated DOrA * [[HRT Dora]], Croatian music festival and preselection venue for the Eurovision Song Contest * [[Hurricane Dora]], 1964 hurricane which was the first and last to hit Jacksonville, Florida * [[Tropical Storm Dora (disambiguation)]], various storms in the Atlantic, Pacific and Indian Oceans * In computer networking, DORA is an acronym used to describe the Discover, Offer, Request, Acknowledge process in the [[DHCP]] protocol * Dora, a designated [[Japanese Mahjong#Dora|bonus tile used in Japanese Mahjong]] * [[Titular diocese of Dora]] * [[Dumb Dora]], a slang term from the 1920s meaning ''idiotic woman'' * Dora, a medieval title of the [[Indian feudalism#Telangana|feudal landlord in the Telangana region]] of India * {{SS|Dora}}, a London and South Western Railway passenger ship ==See also== *[[Doralice]] *[[Dorothea (disambiguation)]] *[[Theodora (disambiguation)]] *[[Dorie (disambiguation)]] {{disambig}}
